Andropogon hallii

   [3204.jpg]
    Authority   Hackel
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names sand bluestem, anadelfia da areia
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3204

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A bunchgrass vigorously producing rhizomes. Culms may
   reach 1-2 m in height. USES Used as an erosion control agent. GROWING
   PERIOD Perennial. COMMON NAMES Sand Bluestem. FURTHER INF Sand bluestem
   is a North American prairie grass usually found on sandy soils.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Heath M 1985 pp 180 [TEXT, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 78 [TEXT, DRA, USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 6 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]

